(150, 2, '2021-05-25 09:23:31', '2021-05-25 09:23:31', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To change the title of a single product page in WooCommerce, you can use the <code>woocommerce_single_product_title</code> filter hook in WordPress. Here\'s an example code snippet that you can add to your theme\'s <code>functions.php</code> file:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>function custom_product_title( $title ) {\r\n    $new_title = \'New Title Here\';\r\n    return $new_title;\r\n}\r\nadd_filter( \'woocommerce_single_product_title\', \'custom_product_title\' );\r</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This code replaces the default product title with a new title <code>New Title Here</code>. You can modify this code to change the title to any other text or variable that you want to display.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once you have added this code, the new title will be displayed on the single product page. If you want to change the title for a specific product, you can modify the code to include a conditional statement based on the product ID or any other criteria.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Also, you can use the following way to change the title.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>remove_action( \'woocommerce_single_product_summary\',\'woocommerce_template_single_title\', 5 );\nadd_action( \'woocommerce_single_product_summary\', \'sgl_template_single_title\', 99 );\nfunction sgl_template_single_title() {\n   \n    the_title( \'&lt;h3 class=\"tt product_title entry-title\"&gt;\', \'&lt;/h3&gt;\' );\n}</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons\"><!-- wp:button -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https://codenskills.com/sql-query-to-get-duplicate-value/\">SQL query to get duplicate value</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons -->', 'How to Change Single Product Page Title in WooCommerce', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-change-single-product-page-title', '', '', '2025-03-21 10:57:00', '2025-03-21 10:57:00', '', 0, 'https://mycodingsolution.com/?p=150', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(152, 2, '2021-05-25 09:26:42', '2021-05-25 09:26:42', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To clear the cache in Laravel using CLI, you can use the <code>php artisan cache:clear</code> command. This command clears the application cache, including the cache of compiled views, routes, and configuration files.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here are the steps to clear the cache in Laravel using CLI:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Open the command prompt or terminal on your computer.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Navigate to the root directory of your Laravel application.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Run the following command:</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Wait for the command to finish executing. Once it is done, you should see a message confirming that the cache has been cleared.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>php artisan cache:clear\r</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can also clear specific caches using CLI, such as the view cache, route cache, and config cache, by running the following commands:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>php artisan view:clear\r\nphp artisan route:clear\r\nphp artisan config:clear</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>By clearing the cache, you can ensure that your Laravel application runs smoothly and that any changes you make to the code are reflected immediately.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons\"><!-- wp:button -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https://codenskills.com/how-to-change-single-product-page-title/\">How To Change Single Product Page Title</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons -->', 'How TO Clear Chache in Laravel By CLI', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-clear-chache-in-laravel-by-cli', '', '', '2025-03-21 10:55:32', '2025-03-21 10:55:32', '', 0, 'https://mycodingsolution.com/?p=152', 0, 'post', '', 0);
