(154, 2, '2021-05-25 09:31:08', '2021-05-25 09:31:08', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can redirect a URL permanently (301 redirects) using .htaccess the file. To create a 301 redirect, you need to add a redirect rule in the <code>.htaccess</code> file.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here is an example of how to redirect <code>old-url</code> to <code>new-url</code> using <code>.htaccess</code>:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>Redirect 301 /old-url /new-url\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the above code, <code>old-url</code> is the URL you want to redirect, and <code>new-url</code> is the URL where you want to redirect. The <code>301</code> indicates that the redirection is permanent, which will update search engines and browsers with the new URL.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can add multiple redirect rules in <code>.htaccess</code> file for multiple URLs that you want to redirect.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Additionally, you can also use regular expressions in <code>.htaccess</code> file to redirect URLs based on patterns. This is useful if you want to redirect multiple URLs that match a particular pattern.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here is an example of how to redirect URLs based on a pattern:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>RewriteEngine On\nRewriteRule ^old-url(.*)$ /new-url$1 &#91;R=301,L]\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And Final Code is given below.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>RewriteEngine On\n\nRewriteCond %{HTTPS} off \nRewriteRule ^(.*)$ https://%{HTTP_HOST}%{REQUEST_URI} &#91;L,R=301]\nRewriteCond %{HTTP_HOST} ^www\\.(.*)$ &#91;NC]\nRewriteRule ^(.*)$ https://%1%{REQUEST_URI} &#91;R=301,QSA,NC,L]\n\nRedirect 301 /old-url /new-url</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the above code, <code>^old-url(.*)$</code> is the pattern for the URLs you want to redirect, and <code>/new-url$1</code> is the URL where you want to redirect? <code>$1</code> is a back-reference to the matched pattern, which allows you to preserve any additional URL path information that follows <code>old-url</code>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Make sure to back up your <code>.htaccess</code> file before making any changes and test the redirect thoroughly to ensure it works as expected.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons\"><!-- wp:button -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https://codenskills.com/how-to-clear-chache-in-laravel-by-cli/\">How TO Clear Chache in Laravel By CLI</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons -->', 'How To Redirect 301 URL by .htaccess', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-redirect-301-url-by-htaccess', '', '', '2025-04-01 11:44:18', '2025-04-01 06:14:18', '', 0, 'https://mycodingsolution.com/?p=154', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(156, 2, '2021-05-25 09:32:48', '2021-05-25 09:32:48', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>WordPress provides a function called <code>WP_Query()</code> to fetch custom post types based on specific criteria.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here\'s an example of how to fetch custom post types with the <code>WP_Query()</code> function:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;?php\n$args = array(\r\n    \'post_type\' => \'custom_post_type\',\r\n    \'posts_per_page\' => 10,\r\n    \'orderby\' => \'date\',\r\n    \'order\' => \'DESC\'\r\n);\r\n\r\n$query = new WP_Query($args);\r\n\r\nif ( $query->have_posts() ) {\r\n    while ( $query->have_posts() ) {\r\n        $query->the_post();\r\n        // Display post content\r\n    }\r\n    wp_reset_postdata();\r\n} else {\r\n    // No posts found\r\n}\r\n\n?></code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the above example, the <code>post_type</code> the parameter is set to the name of the custom post type that you want to fetch. Other parameters are used to specify the number of posts to display, the order in which to display them, and any other filtering criteria.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once you have defined your query using, WP_Query() you can loop through the results and display the post content as needed. Use the <code>wp_reset_postdata()</code> function to reset the post data after the loop to avoid conflicts with other queries on the page.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Overall, <code>WP_Query()</code> is a powerful and flexible way to retrieve custom post types in WordPress and can be customized to suit your specific needs.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons\"><!-- wp:button -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https://codenskills.com/how-to-redirect-301-url-by-htaccess/\">How To Redirect 301 URL by .htaccess</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons -->', 'WP Custom Post Type Query In WordPress', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'wp-custom-post-type-query-in-wordpress', '', '', '2025-03-21 10:54:24', '2025-03-21 10:54:24', '', 0, 'https://mycodingsolution.com/?p=156', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(158, 2, '2021-05-27 12:22:57', '2021-05-27 12:22:57', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>CSV (Comma-Separated Values) files are widely used for storing and exchanging structured data. Inserting data from a CSV file into a <strong>MySQL database</strong> is a common requirement for web applications. This article explains how to <strong>import multiple records</strong> from a CSV file into a MySQL database using <strong>PHP</strong>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 1: Create a MySQL Database and Table</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Before inserting data, we need to create a MySQL table that matches the structure of our CSV file.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Run the following SQL query to create a sample table:</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>CREATE DATABASE csv_database;\nUSE csv_database;\n\nCREATE TABLE users (\n    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,\n    name VARCHAR(100),\n    email VARCHAR(100)\n);\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This table has three columns: <code>id</code>, <code>name</code>, and <code>email</code>, where <code>id</code> is an auto-incremented primary key.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 2: Insert CSV Data Using PHP</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>PHP provides built-in functions to read CSV files and insert data into a MySQL database.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Basic PHP Code to Insert CSV Data into MySQL</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;?php\n\n// Database connection\n$mysqli = new mysqli(\"localhost\", \"root\", \"password\", \"csv_database\");\n\nif ($mysqli->connect_error) {\n    die(\"Connection failed: \" . $mysqli->connect_error);\n}\n\n// Open CSV file\n$file = fopen(\"data.csv\", \"r\");\n\n// Skip the first row if it contains column headers\nfgetcsv($file);\n\n// Read each row and insert it into the database\nwhile (($row = fgetcsv($file, 1000, \",\")) !== FALSE) {\n    $sql = \"INSERT INTO users (name, email) VALUES (\'$row&#91;0]\', \'$row&#91;1]\')\";\n    $mysqli->query($sql);\n}\n\n// Close file and database connection\nfclose($file);\n$mysqli->close();\n\necho \"Data imported successfully!\";\n?>\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Explanation of the PHP Code:</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Connects to MySQL</strong> using <code>mysqli</code>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Opens the CSV file</strong> using <code>fopen()</code>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Reads each row</strong> using <code>fgetcsv()</code>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Inserts data into the database</strong> using an <code>INSERT INTO</code> query.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Closes the file and database connection</strong> after completion.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 3: Optimize for Large CSV Files</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For large CSV files, inserting data <strong>row by row</strong> can be slow. Instead, we can <strong>bulk insert</strong> multiple rows in a single query to improve performance.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Optimized PHP Code for Bulk CSV Import</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;?php\n\n$mysqli = new mysqli(\"localhost\", \"root\", \"password\", \"csv_database\");\n\n$file = fopen(\"data.csv\", \"r\");\n$values = &#91;];\n\n// Skip the first row if it contains column headers\nfgetcsv($file);\n\nwhile (($row = fgetcsv($file, 1000, \",\")) !== FALSE) {\n    $values&#91;] = \"(\'\" . implode(\"\',\'\", array_map(\'addslashes\', $row)) . \"\')\";\n}\n\n// Bulk insert query\nif (!empty($values)) {\n    $sql = \"INSERT INTO users (name, email) VALUES \" . implode(\",\", $values);\n    $mysqli->query($sql);\n}\n\nfclose($file);\n$mysqli->close();\n\necho \"Bulk data imported successfully!\";\n?>\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Why Use Bulk Insert?</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Inserts multiple rows in one query</strong>, significantly improving speed.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Reduces database connection overhead</strong>, especially for large datasets.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 4: Test the Data Import</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After running the PHP script, check if the data has been inserted correctly by running the following SQL query:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>SELECT * FROM users;\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If everything is set up correctly, you should see the imported data in your database.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Best Practices for CSV Data Import in PHP</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>‚úÖ <strong>Use Bulk Insert:</strong> It improves performance when handling large CSV files.<br>‚úÖ <strong>Validate Data Before Importing:</strong> Ensure the CSV file has the correct format.<br>‚úÖ <strong>Optimize Database Indexing:</strong> Indexing speeds up queries after data insertion.<br>‚úÖ <strong>Handle Special Characters:</strong> Use <code>addslashes()</code> to prevent errors.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons\"><!-- wp:button -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https://codenskills.com/wp-custom-post-type-query-in-wordpress/\">WP Custom Post Type Query In WordPress</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons -->', 'How To Insert Multiple data in the database from CSV', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-insert-multiple-data-in-database-from-csv', '', '', '2025-03-03 09:47:27', '2025-03-03 09:47:27', '', 0, 'https://mycodingsolution.com/?p=158', 0, 'post', '', 0),
