(290, 2, '2021-08-30 09:31:53', '2021-08-30 09:31:53', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>TWhen building a website, it\'s often useful to determine whether a link is external or internal. External links direct users to a different domain, whereas internal links keep them within the same site. To enhance user experience and SEO, many developers prefer opening external links in a new tab while keeping internal links unchanged.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In this article, we will explore how to check if a link is external using both <strong>jQuery</strong> and <strong>pure JavaScript</strong>. We will also discuss different approaches to handling external links for better usability.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Why Identify External Links?</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Before diving into the code, let‚Äôs explore why identifying external links is important:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Better User Experience</strong> ‚Äì Keeping users on the same tab for internal links while opening external links in a new tab prevents them from losing track of your website.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>SEO Considerations</strong> ‚Äì Adding <code>rel=\"nofollow\"</code> to external links prevents search engines from following them, reducing the risk of passing link equity to unknown sites.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Security</strong> ‚Äì External links can be potential security risks. Identifying them allows developers to add security attributes like <code>rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"</code>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Checking If a Link is External Using jQuery</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>jQuery provides a simple way to loop through all <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> tags and check their hostname. Here‚Äôs a script that does this:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;script src=\"https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.6.0.min.js\">&lt;/script>\n&lt;script>\n  $(document).ready(function () {\n    var currentDomain = new RegExp(location.hostname);\n\n    $(\'a\').each(function () {\n      var link = $(this).attr(\'href\');\n\n      if (link &amp;&amp; !currentDomain.test(link)) {\n        $(this).attr(\'target\', \'_blank\').attr(\'rel\', \'noopener noreferrer\');\n      }\n    });\n  });\n&lt;/script>\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Explanation of the Code:</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We create a <code>RegExp</code> object using the current domain (<code>location.hostname</code>).</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We loop through all <code>&lt;a></code> elements using <code>each()</code>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>If a link does <strong>not</strong> contain the current domain, it is considered external.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We add the <code>target=\"_blank\"</code> attribute to open it in a new tab and <code>rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"</code> for security.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Checking If a Link is External Using Pure JavaScript</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you prefer not to use jQuery, you can achieve the same functionality using vanilla JavaScript:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;script>\n  document.addEventListener(\'DOMContentLoaded\', function () {\n    var links = document.querySelectorAll(\'a\');\n\n    links.forEach(function (link) {\n      if (link.hostname &amp;&amp; link.hostname !== window.location.hostname) {\n        link.setAttribute(\'target\', \'_blank\');\n        link.setAttribute(\'rel\', \'noopener noreferrer\');\n      }\n    });\n  });\n&lt;/script>\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>How This Works:</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We wait for the <code>DOMContentLoaded</code> event to ensure the script runs after the page loads.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><code>querySelectorAll(\'a\')</code> selects all anchor tags.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We use <code>forEach()</code> to loop through each link.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>If <code>link.hostname</code> is different from <code>window.location.hostname</code>, it is external.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We then add the necessary attributes (<code>target=\"_blank\"</code> and <code>rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"</code>).</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Enhancing External Link Security</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Apart from opening external links in a new tab, it‚Äôs important to consider security. Here are two key security attributes:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong><code>rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"</code></strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Prevents the new tab from accessing <code>window.opener</code>, which can be exploited in phishing attacks.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><code>noopener</code> prevents the new tab from controlling the original page.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><code>noreferrer</code> prevents referrer information from being sent.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong><code>rel=\"nofollow\"</code></strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Tells search engines not to pass link equity to external sites, which is useful when linking to untrusted sources.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>How to Add These Attributes Using JavaScript:</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>document.querySelectorAll(\'a\').forEach(link => {\n  if (link.hostname !== window.location.hostname) {\n    link.setAttribute(\'rel\', \'nofollow noopener noreferrer\');\n  }\n});</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Alternatively, you can use pure JavaScript with the following code:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>var links = document.querySelectorAll(\'a\');\nfor (var i = 0; i &lt; links.length; i++) {\n  if (links&#91;i].hostname !== window.location.hostname) {\n    links&#91;i].setAttribute(\'target\', \'_blank\');\n  }\n}\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Final Thoughts</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Checking if a link is external or internal is a simple but effective way to improve user experience, SEO, and security.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Key Takeaways:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Use <strong>JavaScript or jQuery</strong> to check if a link is external.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Open external links in a <strong>new tab</strong> (<code>target=\"_blank\"</code>) for better user experience.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Add <code>rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"</code> for <strong>security</strong> and <code>rel=\"nofollow\"</code> for <strong>SEO</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Use <strong>CSS</strong> to visually highlight external links.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons\"><!-- wp:button -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https://codenskills.com/how-to-disable-theme-editor-and-plugin-editor-in-wordpress-admin-panel/\">How to disable Theme Editor and Plugin Editor in the WordPress admin panel?</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons -->', 'Check if links are external with jQuery/javascript.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'check-if-links-are-external-with-jquery-javascript', '', '', '2025-03-03 08:04:49', '2025-03-03 08:04:49', '', 0, 'https://mycodingsolution.com/?p=290', 0, 'post', '', 0),
