(625, 1, '2025-02-05 14:11:48', '2025-02-05 14:11:48', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When working on multiple projects locally, accessing them via <code>http://localhost/projectname</code> can be inconvenient. Setting up <strong>Virtual Hosts</strong> in XAMPP allows you to create custom domain names like <code>codenskills.local</code>, making development easier and more professional.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This guide will walk you through <strong>setting up virtual hosts in XAMPP</strong> to run multiple sites locally using custom domain names.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>What is a Virtual Host?</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A <strong>Virtual Host</strong> allows you to assign a custom domain name (e.g., <code><code>codenskills</code>.local</code>) to a project folder inside XAMPP‚Äôs <code>htdocs</code>. Instead of accessing your project via <code>http://localhost/<code>codenskills</code></code>, you can access it via <code>http://codenskills.local</code>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Virtual Hosts are commonly used to:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Run multiple websites on a local server.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Mimic live website domains for accurate testing.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Improve organization when working with multiple projects.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Why Use Virtual Hosts for Development?</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li> <strong>Professional Development:</strong> Simulates a real domain environment (<code><code>codenskills</code>.local</code>).</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li> <strong>Easier Site Management:</strong> Avoids long URLs like <code>localhost/<code>codenskills</code></code>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li> <strong>Better Testing:</strong> Treats <code>localhost</code> differently from a real domain, so virtual hosts ensure smoother migration to live servers.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li> <strong>Multi-Site Support:</strong> Allows you to work on multiple installations simultaneously.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 1: Enable Virtual Hosts in Apache</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>By default, Apache\'s Virtual Hosts feature is disabled in XAMPP. To enable it:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Open the Apache configuration file:</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code><code>E:\\xampp8.2\\apache\\conf\\httpd.conf</code></code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Search for the following line:</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code><code>#Include conf/extra/httpd-vhosts.conf</code></code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Remove the <code>#</code> at the beginning to uncomment the line:</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code><code>Include conf/extra/httpd-vhosts.conf</code></code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Save and close the file.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 2: Create a Virtual Host Configuration</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Next, we define the custom domain in Apache\'s virtual host configuration file.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Open the <strong>Virtual Hosts file</strong>:</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code><code>E:\\xampp8.2\\apache\\conf\\extra\\httpd-vhosts.conf</code></code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Add the following code at the bottom of the file to create a virtual host for your site:</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;VirtualHost *:80&gt;\n    DocumentRoot \"E:/xampp8.2/htdocs\"\n    ServerName localhost\n    &lt;Directory \"E:/xampp8.2/htdocs\"&gt;\n        AllowOverride All\n        Require all granted\n    &lt;/Directory&gt;\n&lt;/VirtualHost&gt;\n\n&lt;VirtualHost *:80&gt;\n    ServerAdmin webmaster@localhost\n    DocumentRoot \"E:/xampp8.2/htdocs/mywebsite\"\n    ServerName mywebsite.local\n    ServerAlias www.mywebsite.local\n    ErrorLog \"logs/mywebsite-error.log\"\n    CustomLog \"logs/mywebsite-access.log\" common\n\n    &lt;Directory \"E:/xampp8.2/htdocs/mywebsite\"&gt;\n        AllowOverride All\n        Require all granted\n    &lt;/Directory&gt;\n&lt;/VirtualHost&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Save and close the file.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 3: Update the Windows Hosts File</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To access <code>codenskills.local</code>, we need to map it in the Windows <code>hosts</code> file.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Open <strong>Notepad as Administrator</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Open this file:</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code><code>C:\\Windows\\System32\\drivers\\etc\\hosts</code></code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Add this line at the bottom:</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code><code>127.0.0.1 codenskills.local</code></code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Save and close the file.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 4: Restart Apache and Test the Virtual Host</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Open <strong>XAMPP Control Panel</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Click <strong>Stop</strong> next to Apache, then <strong>Start</strong> again.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Open a browser and go to:</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code><code>http://codenskills.local</code></code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>If everything is configured correctly, you should see the contents of your website folder.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Conclusion</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Setting up <strong>Virtual Hosts in XAMPP</strong> makes local development much easier. Instead of navigating to <code>localhost/<code>codenskills</code></code>, you can simply type <code><code>codenskills</code>.local</code> in the browser.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>By following these steps, you can create multiple sites locally, streamline your workflow, and prepare for live deployment more efficiently. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons\"><!-- wp:button -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https://codenskills.com/how-to-redirect-301-url-by-htaccess/\">How To Redirect 301 URL by .htaccess</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons -->', 'How to Set Up Virtual Hosts in XAMPP for Local Development', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-set-up-virtual-hosts-in-xampp-for-local-development', '', '', '2025-02-06 11:14:23', '2025-02-06 11:14:23', '', 0, 'https://codenskills.com/?p=625', 0, 'post', '', 0),
