(657, 1, '2025-02-06 11:28:43', '2025-02-06 11:28:43', '<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Fixing AnyDesk on Ubuntu 22.04 LTS: A Step-by-Step Guide</strong></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ubuntu 22.04 LTS (Long Term Support) is the latest version of Ubuntu, and while it brings a host of improvements and new features, it can occasionally cause compatibility issues with third-party applications. One such application is AnyDesk, a popular remote desktop software. If you\'ve recently upgraded to Ubuntu 22.04 LTS and are experiencing issues with AnyDesk, you are not alone. Many users have reported problems where the application simply refuses to open or crashes immediately after launching.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you\'re an AnyDesk user on Ubuntu 22.04 LTS and you\'re looking for a solution, you\'re in the right place. In this blog post, we‚Äôll take a look at why this issue occurs and provide a simple step-by-step solution to get AnyDesk running smoothly again.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Why Does AnyDesk Stop Working After Upgrading to Ubuntu 22.04 LTS?</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After upgrading to Ubuntu 22.04 LTS, some users find that AnyDesk either doesn\'t launch or crashes after a few seconds. This problem typically arises due to changes in the underlying libraries that AnyDesk depends on. One of the most common causes of this issue is a missing or outdated library that AnyDesk relies on to function properly.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One such library is <strong>libpangox-1.0-0</strong>, which provides the necessary support for certain graphical applications. AnyDesk uses this library for rendering its user interface, and if the library is incompatible or missing, AnyDesk fails to start.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading --