(737, 1, '2025-03-21 10:56:59', '2025-03-21 10:56:59', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To change the title of a single product page in WooCommerce, you can use the <code>woocommerce_single_product_title</code> filter hook in WordPress. Here\'s an example code snippet that you can add to your theme\'s <code>functions.php</code> file:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>function custom_product_title( $title ) {\r\n    $new_title = \'New Title Here\';\r\n    return $new_title;\r\n}\r\nadd_filter( \'woocommerce_single_product_title\', \'custom_product_title\' );\r</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This code replaces the default product title with a new title <code>New Title Here</code>. You can modify this code to change the title to any other text or variable that you want to display.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once you have added this code, the new title will be displayed on the single product page. If you want to change the title for a specific product, you can modify the code to include a conditional statement based on the product ID or any other criteria.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Also, you can use the following way to change the title.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>remove_action( \'woocommerce_single_product_summary\',\'woocommerce_template_single_title\', 5 );\nadd_action( \'woocommerce_single_product_summary\', \'sgl_template_single_title\', 99 );\nfunction sgl_template_single_title() {\n   \n    the_title( \'&lt;h3 class=\"tt product_title entry-title\"&gt;\', \'&lt;/h3&gt;\' );\n}</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons\"><!-- wp:button -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https://codenskills.com/sql-query-to-get-duplicate-value/\">SQL query to get duplicate value</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons -->', 'How to Change Single Product Page Title in WooCommerce', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '150-revision-v1', '', '', '2025-03-21 10:56:59', '2025-03-21 10:56:59', '', 150, 'https://codenskills.com/?p=737', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(738, 1, '2025-03-21 11:03:36', '2025-03-21 11:03:36', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To get duplicate values from a table in SQL, you can use the <code>GROUP BY</code> clause with the <code>HAVING</code> clause. Here\'s an example SQL query that retrieves duplicate values from a table named <code>tbl_app_users </code>:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>SELECT email, COUNT(*) c FROM tbl_app_users GROUP BY email HAVING c &gt; 1 </code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Replace <code>column_name</code> with the name of the column that you want to check for duplicates. This SQL query groups the rows by the specified column and counts the number of occurrences of each value. The <code>HAVING</code> clause filters the results to show only the values that have more than one occurrence, indicating that they are duplicates.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can modify this SQL query to suit your needs by changing the table name, column name, and any additional conditions that you want to apply.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons\"><!-- wp:button -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https://codenskills.com/checkout-page-input-and-add-class-in-woo-commerce-via-hooks/\">Checkout page input and add class in woo-commerce via hooks</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons -->', 'How to Find Duplicate Values in SQL', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '117-revision-v1', '', '', '2025-03-21 11:03:36', '2025-03-21 11:03:36', '', 117, 'https://codenskills.com/?p=738', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(739, 1, '2025-03-24 11:10:12', '2025-03-24 11:10:12', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Filament is a modern admin panel framework for Laravel that simplifies the creation of user-friendly dashboards and interfaces. Whether you\'re building a small application or a complex system, Filament provides powerful tools to streamline your workflow. This guide will walk you through the installation process step by step.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Prerequisites</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Before installing Filament, ensure your system meets the following requirements:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>PHP</strong>: Version 8.1 or higher</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Laravel</strong>: Version 10.0 or higher</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Livewire</strong>: Version 3.0 or higher</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step-by-Step Installation Guide</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 1: Install Laravel</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Begin by creating a new Laravel project. Run the following command:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>composer create-project laravel/laravel filament-laravel\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once installed, configure your database connection in the&nbsp;<code>.env</code>&nbsp;file and migrate the default tables:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>php artisan migrate</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 2: Install Filament</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Add Filament to your Laravel project using Composer:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>composer require filament/filament:\"^3.0-stable\" -W</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Next, install the Filament Panel Builder, which sets up necessary service providers and configuration files:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>php artisan filament:install --panels</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This command automatically registers&nbsp;<code>AdminPanelProvider</code>&nbsp;in your application.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 3: Create an Admin User</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To access the admin panel, you need to create an admin user. Run this command:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>php artisan make:filament-user</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Follow the prompts to enter details like name, email, and password.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 4: Access the Admin Panel</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Start your Laravel application server:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>php artisan serve</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Visit&nbsp;<code>http://localhost:8000/admin</code>&nbsp;in your browser and log in using the credentials created earlier.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Features of Filament</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Filament comes with pre-installed packages like:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Form Builder</strong>: Create dynamic forms with built-in validation.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Table Builder</strong>: Display data in tables with sorting and filtering options.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Notifications</strong>: Send alerts and messages within the admin panel.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Widgets</strong>: Add customizable dashboard elements.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>These tools make it easy to build scalable and interactive admin panels.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Customizing Filament</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Filament allows extensive customization:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Create custom resources for managing models.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Build unique pages for specific functionalities.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Implement role-based access control for managing permissions.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Conclusion</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Installing and configuring Filament Admin Panel in Laravel is straightforward, enabling developers to focus on building robust applications without worrying about backend design complexities. With its powerful components and ease of use, Filament is ideal for creating modern admin dashboards.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Start exploring Filament today and take your Laravel projects to the next level!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons\"><!-- wp:button -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https://codenskills.com/must-know-laravel-commands-for-developers-boost-productivity-efficiency/\">Must-Know Laravel Commands for Developers</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'How to Install Filament Admin Panel in Laravel', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-install-filament-admin-panel-in-laravel', '', '', '2025-03-24 11:19:59', '2025-03-24 11:19:59', '', 0, 'https://codenskills.com/?p=739', 0, 'post', '', 0),
